!begin_node (!kw [html_quotes])
!html_name  cmd_html_quotes

Define output format of quotation marks in HTML

!begin_xlist [(!TYPEPOSITION)]

!item [(!TYPEPOSITION)] (!COMMAND), (!PREAMBLE)

!item [(!SYNTAX)] (!T)!/html_quotes [(!NAME)](!t)

!item [(!DESCRIPTION)]
Use this command to define the output format of quotation marks in HTML. [(!NAME)] accepts the following parameters.

!begin_description

!item [tags]
HTML quotations will be output as (!code [<q>]) or (!code [</q>]) respectively. We recommend to control the replacement characters for the quote tags in various languages in a .CSS file.

(!EXAMPLE)
Here are CSS commands for various quotation marks in several languages.
!ifdest [asc,stg]
!begin_verbatim
:lang(cs) { quotes:"\00BB"      "\00AB" !\
            "\203A"      "\2039";      }
:lang(de) { quotes:"\00BB"      "\00AB" !\
            "\203A"      "\2039";      }
:lang(en) { quotes:"\201C"      "\201D" !\
            "\2018"      "\2019";      }
:lang(fr) { quotes:"\00AB\00A0" "\00A0\00BB" !\
            "\2039\00A0" "\00A0\203A"; }

q:before   {content:open-quote;  color:#2E4793;}
q:after    {content:close-quote; color:#2E4793;}
q q:before {content:open-quote;  color:Green;  }
q q:after  {content:close-quote; color:Green;  }
!end_verbatim
!else
!begin_verbatim
:lang(cs) { quotes:"\00BB"      "\00AB"      "\203A"      "\2039";      }
:lang(de) { quotes:"\00BB"      "\00AB"      "\203A"      "\2039";      }
:lang(en) { quotes:"\201C"      "\201D"      "\2018"      "\2019";      }
:lang(fr) { quotes:"\00AB\00A0" "\00A0\00BB" "\2039\00A0" "\00A0\203A"; }

q:before   { content:open-quote;  color:#2E4793; }
q:after    { content:close-quote; color:#2E4793; }
q q:before { content:open-quote;  color:Green;   }
q q:after  { content:close-quote; color:Green;   }
!end_verbatim
!endif
(!EXAMPLE_END)

!item [classic]
HTML quotations will be output as (!code [&quot;]).

!end_description

!item [(!EXISTSSINCE)] Release~6.5.20

!item [(!SEEALSO)]
(!KW [html_modern_layout])

!end_xlist

!end_node

